ct-fit:cover;object-position:center;opacity:0;transition-delay:500ms\"/><picture><source srcSet=\"/static/80beb15be00784f69ce10c0a39cc07f7/85b06/Image-SA-YES-Grant.png 256w,\n/static/80beb15be00784f69ce10c0a39cc07f7/bc282/Image-SA-YES-Grant.png 512w,\n/static/80beb15be00784f69ce10c0a39cc07f7/f1720/Image-SA-YES-Grant.png 1024w,\n/static/80beb15be00784f69ce10c0a39cc07f7/5ece7/Image-SA-YES-Grant.png 1200w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\"/><img sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" srcSet=\"/static/80beb15be00784f69ce10c0a39cc07f7/85b06/Image-SA-YES-Grant.png 256w,\n/static/80beb15be00784f69ce10c0a39cc07f7/bc282/Image-SA-YES-Grant.png 512w,\n/static/80beb15be00784f69ce10c0a39cc07f7/f1720/Image-SA-YES-Grant.png 1024w,\n/static/80beb15be00784f69ce10c0a39cc07f7/5ece7/Image-SA-YES-Grant.png 1200w\" src=\"/static/80beb15be00784f69ce10c0a39cc07f7/f1720/Image-SA-YES-Grant.png\" alt=\"An image of SA YES staff giving a large check to Pleasanton ISD staff for $6000 for STEM programs\" loading=\"eager\" style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;object-position:center;opacity:1;transition:opacity 500ms\"/></picture><noscript><picture><source srcset=\"/static/80beb15be00784f69ce10c0a39cc07f7/85b06/Image-SA-YES-Grant.png 256w,\n/static/80beb15be00784f69ce10c0a39cc07f7/bc282/Image-SA-YES-Grant.png 512w,\n/static/80beb15be00784f69ce10c0a39cc07f7/f1720/Image-SA-YES-Grant.png 1024w,\n/static/80beb15be00784f69ce10c0a39cc07f7/5ece7/Image-SA-YES-Grant.png 1200w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" /><img loading=\"eager\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" srcset=\"/static/80beb15be00784f69ce10c0a39cc07f7/85b06/Image-SA-YES-Grant.png 256w,\n/static/80beb15be00784f69ce10c0a39cc07f7/bc282/Image-SA-YES-Grant.png 512w,\n/static/80beb15be00784f69ce10c0a39cc07f7/f1720/Image-SA-YES-Grant.png 1024w,\n/static/80beb15be00784f69ce10c0a39cc07f7/5ece7/Image-SA-YES-Grant.png 1200w\" src=\"/static/80beb15be00784f69ce10c0a39cc07f7/f1720/Image-SA-YES-Grant.png\" alt=\"An image of SA YES staff giving a large check to Pleasanton ISD staff for $6000 for STEM programs\" style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;opacity:1;width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;object-position:center\"/></picture></noscript></span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>On June 3rd, <strong><a href=\"http://www.sayes.org/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">SA YES</a></strong> presented a STEM grant to <strong><a href=\"https://www.pisd.us/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Pleasanton ISD</a></strong> in the amount of $6,000. The grant is part of a $15,000 allocation of funds by SA YES to STEM needs at Title 1 schools around the San Antonio area as part of their <strong><a href=\"https://sayes.org/yes-grants/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">YES Grant</a></strong> program.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The funds will be used for students in grades 9 through 12 for an introduction to engineering curriculum and supplies. The goal is to create a solid engineering program of study and then focus on adding other STEM programs. With the funding, PISD will be able to purchase a curriculum developed by engineers which helps the staff provide the industry-specific knowledge and skills to the students.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Three <strong><a href=\"https://thepmgrp.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">PM Group</a></strong> employees were on hand for the check presentation. Peggy Wills, <strong><a href=\"https://thepmgrp.com/leadership-kathy-schmitt/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Kathy Schmitt</a></strong> and <strong><a href=\"https://thepmgrp.com/leadership-fran-yanity\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Fran Yanity</a></strong> also serve on the SA YES Board of Directors.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>This latest donation follows a busy season of fundraising for SA YES as well as other YES Grant donations. Earlier in the month, SA YES presented <strong><a href=\"https://pammediaoutreach.org/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">P.A.M. Media Outreach</a></strong> with $4,000 for computers to be used in their program helping inner city youth learn leadership skills.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span class=\"aligncenter wp-image-61918 size-large inline-gatsby-image-wrapper gatsby-image-wrapper\" style=\"position:relative;overflow:hidden;max-width:100%;width:1024px\" data-reactroot=\"\"><span aria-hidden=\"true\" style=\"width:100%;padding-bottom:52.34375%\"></span><img aria-hidden=\"true\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"\" style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;object-position:center;opacity:0;transition-delay:500ms\"/><picture><source srcSet=\"/static/9c52b712b42c36e53ed8171f6ff93a3f/85b06/Image-PAM-Media-Outreach.png 256w,\n/static/9c52b712b42c36e53ed8171f6ff93a3f/bc282/Image-PAM-Media-Outreach.png 512w,\n/static/9c52b712b42c36e53ed8171f6ff93a3f/f1720/Image-PAM-Media-Outreach.png 1024w,\n/static/9c52b712b42c36e53ed8171f6ff93a3f/5ece7/Image-PAM-Media-Outreach.png 1200w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\"/><img sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" srcSet=\"/static/9c52b712b42c36e53ed8171f6ff93a3f/85b06/Image-PAM-Media-Outreach.png 256w,\n/static/9c52b712b42c36e53ed8171f6ff93a3f/bc282/Image-PAM-Media-Outreach.png 512w,\n/static/9c52b712b42c36e53ed8171f6ff93a3f/f1720/Image-PAM-Media-Outreach.png 1024w,\n/static/9c52b712b42c36e53ed8171f6ff93a3f/5ece7/Image-PAM-Media-Outreach.png 1200w\" src=\"/static/9c52b712b42c36e53ed8171f6ff93a3f/f1720/Image-PAM-Media-Outreach.png\" alt=\"An image of SA YES presenting a large check to PAM Media Outreach as part of their SA YES grant program with PAM Media Outreach and SA YES staff and board members present\" loading=\"eager\" style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;object-position:center;opacity:1;transition:opacity 500ms\"/></picture><noscript><picture><source srcset=\"/static/9c52b712b42c36e53ed8171f6ff93a3f/85b06/Image-PAM-Media-Outreach.png 256w,\n/static/9c52b712b42c36e53ed8171f6ff93a3f/bc282/Image-PAM-Media-Outreach.png 512w,\n/static/9c52b712b42c36e53ed8171f6ff93a3f/f1720/Image-PAM-Media-Outreach.png 1024w,\n/static/9c52b712b42c36e53ed8171f6ff93a3f/5ece7/Image-PAM-Media-Outreach.png 1200w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" /><img loading=\"eager\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" srcset=\"/static/9c52b712b42c36e53ed8171f6ff93a3f/85b06/Image-PAM-Media-Outreach.png 256w,\n/static/9c52b712b42c36e53ed8171f6ff93a3f/bc282/Image-PAM-Media-Outreach.png 512w,\n/static/9c52b712b42c36e53ed8171f6ff93a3f/f1720/Image-PAM-Media-Outreach.png 1024w,\n/static/9c52b712b42c36e53ed8171f6ff93a3f/5ece7/Image-PAM-Media-Outreach.png 1200w\" src=\"/static/9c52b712b42c36e53ed8171f6ff93a3f/f1720/Image-PAM-Media-Outreach.png\" alt=\"An image of SA YES presenting a large check to PAM Media Outreach as part of their SA YES grant program with PAM Media Outreach and SA YES staff and board members present\" style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;opacity:1;width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;object-position:center\"/></picture></noscript></span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>“I am honored to be able to provide Pleasanton ISD and PAM Media Outreach much-needed funds to further their programs and goals to help students,” stated <strong><a href=\"https://sayes.org/board-of-directors/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Danielle Gunter</a></strong>, Executive Director of SA YES. “STEM is the future and all students should have the resources they need to make strides in this area,” continued Gunter.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://thepmgrp.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><strong>About The PM Group</strong></a>: The PM Group was founded in 1988. For over 33 years, the agency has continued to grow and is San Antonio’s largest marketing and advertising agency. The PM Group’s client roster spans numerous industries including home services, automotive, CPG, entertainment and sports marketing, legal, business services, non-profits, real estate and fitness. For two consecutive years now, the Agency has set annual revenue records with the addition of six new clients and through the continued success of our existing clients. Additionally, the agency hosts their annual Charity Gala that to date has raised millions of dollars for local San Antonio area non-profit organizations in the last 15 years! In 2020 alone, the Agency donated over $1,050,000 to local non-profits. It is our way of giving back to the community that we so humbly serve.</p>\n","title":"SA YES Presents YES Grants to Fund STEM Needs","seo":{"breadcrumbs":[{"text":"SA YES Presents YES Grants to Fund STEM Needs","url":"/sa-yes-presents-yes-grants-to-fund-stem-needs/"}],"title":"SA YES Funds STEM Education | The PM Group","metaDesc":"SA YES presented YES Grants to Pleasanton ISD and PAM Media Outreach to fund the development of STEM programs.","focuskw":"YES Grants","metaKeywords":"","metaRobotsNoindex":"index","metaRobotsNofollow":"follow","opengraphTitle":"SA YES Presents YES Grants to Fund STEM Needs | The PM Group","opengraphDescription":"SA YES presented YES Grants to Pleasanton ISD and PAM Media Outreach to fund the development of STEM programs.","opengraphImage":{"altText":"An image of SA YES staff giving a large check to Pleasanton ISD staff for $6000 for STEM programs","sourceUrl":"https://thepmgroup.flywheelsites.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/Image-SA-YES-Grant.png","srcSet":"https://thepmgroup.flywheelsites.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/Image-SA-YES-Grant-300x158.png 300w, https://thepmgroup.flywheelsites.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/Image-SA-YES-Grant-1024x538.png 1024w, https://thepmgroup.flywheelsites.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/Image-SA-YES-Grant-768x403.png 768w, https://thepmgroup.flywheelsites.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/Image-SA-YES-Grant.png 1200w"},"twitterTitle":"SA YES 